        {
            "blockname": "During Placement",
            "name": "Learning Effectively",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Learning Effectively",
                    "space_after": true,
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Learning happens every day. All the skills and knowledge we use we have learned, however we often take it for granted. There are different earning styles, most people use a combination of learning styles to facilitate their learning."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Find out which learning styles best facilitate your learning. You can reflect on the things you learn and how your learning was enhanced – it may be the reading material or the way the educator or mentor explained something in particular or even the way you chose to link the theory with the practical skill. Learning how you learn will support your capacity to learn."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Practice, practice, practice! The best way to know if you can do something is to practice is – be hands on and develop the confidence to try."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Stay focused and motivated. A healthy diet influences your mood and motivation. Eating plenty of fruits and vegetables, exercising regularly and sleeping well will be particularly useful to ensure you have a good mood and motivation to learn."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Ask for help if you need it. Feel free to say when you do not understand and discuss your scope of practice with your educator and mentor. The educator or mentor will seek to challenge you. This is good for your learning but only you will know if the challenge is inspiring or burdensome."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Self-learn. It is your responsibility to direct your own learning. Focus on learning and it is likely you learn the more."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Develop good relationships with your mentors and educators. You cannot make anyone like you but being polite and respectful shows you are putting in the effort and most people mimic behaviour when relationships are being developed."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Reflection is good practice. You may want to keep a learning diary where you summarise your experiences and summarise the things you have learned every day."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Be SMART. Set small, measurable, achievable, realistic goals every week. Have a good discussion with your educator or mentor about you want to achieve your goals and enjoy your journey."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "You never really fail, you just learn differently. Be determined to get better if your performance is below par."
                                }
                            ],
                            "subtitle": "Tips for learning effectively in practice"
                        }
