        {
            "blockname": "During Placement",
            "name": "Reasonable Adjustments",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Are your RA successful?",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "You can review your RA and have a discussion with your educator/mentor about how well they are helping you."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Do you need additional support?",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "If you think your RA are not adequate, have a conversation with the Learning Support Tutor about why you will want to changes some things. Then talk you’re your mentor or educator about that changes. Consider how the RA can be introduced. Some RA may not be accessible in particular environments.",
                            "space_after": true
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "You know you best!",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Everyone is an individual with unique characteristics, strengths and needs. People may not fully understand your individual needs however you know you best. You can explain your feelings and difficulties experienced to your practice educator as many times as you need.  If you need more support, re-explain your issues with your practice educator. You can also contact the disabilities team and placement team at university for support and ideas."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
